## What Problem This Solves

Fixes #95597.

Codex native `PostToolUse` relay only treated `after_tool_call` hooks as local post-tool work, so loaded Codex tool-result middleware such as Tokenjuice could be skipped for native Codex tool completions.

## Why This Change Was Made

The native Codex relay now treats active Codex `agentToolResultMiddleware` registrations as post-tool work. For native `PostToolUse`, the relay gives middleware an OpenClaw-shaped view of Codex's stable `tool_response` payload.

When middleware returns rewritten text, the relay maps that result onto Codex's supported `PostToolUse` feedback path: exit code 2 with feedback on stderr. Codex records that feedback as the model-visible replacement output, which keeps Tokenjuice-style compaction effective without adding broader plugin-loader ownership changes. Existing `after_tool_call` observers still receive the raw native hook payload.

The native coercion keeps command output in `content` rather than duplicating it into `details`, so actual Tokenjuice middleware can compact large output without tripping middleware result-size validation.

Codex contract checked:

- `../codex/codex-rs/core/src/tools/registry.rs:573-625`
- `../codex/codex-rs/hooks/src/events/post_tool_use.rs:190-272`
- `../codex/codex-rs/core/src/hook_runtime.rs:257-285`

## User Impact

Tokenjuice and other loaded Codex tool-result middleware can observe native Codex tool results and replace model-visible command output again without requiring unrelated `after_tool_call` hooks.

## Evidence

- Exact Tokenjuice native relay replay below: registered the real bundled Tokenjuice middleware in the native relay, replayed a Codex `PostToolUse` Bash result with 68,289 chars of output, and observed `{ exitCode: 2, stdoutBytes: 0, stderrChars: 1126 }` with a Tokenjuice summary preview.
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.test.ts`
- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core.tsbuildinfo`
- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo`
- `git diff --check`
- `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`
- CI on amended SHA `4172e9ae120d4dfe1946da47c26194282edbf4e5`: `Real behavior proof`, `Auto response`, `Labeler`, and `ClawSweeper Dispatch` passed.
- One autoreview round found that the first trimmed patch discarded middleware results; this revision captures returned middleware output and maps changed text to Codex feedback. Per draft-PR guardrails, I did not run another autoreview loop.

### Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: Native Codex `PostToolUse` now runs active Codex tool-result middleware and returns changed middleware text through Codex's feedback replacement path.

Real environment tested: Local Codex worktree, rebased onto current `origin/main`, with actual bundled Tokenjuice middleware registered into the native hook relay.

Exact steps or command run after this patch: the exact Tokenjuice native relay replay command below; `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.test.ts`; `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core.tsbuildinfo`; `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo`; `git diff --check`; `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`.

Evidence after fix: Focused native relay Vitest passed with 78 tests, including coverage for active middleware relay registration, middleware event/context coercion, unchanged middleware no-op, and rewritten middleware output returning `{ stdout: "", stderr: "compacted output\n", exitCode: 2 }`. A direct local replay with real Tokenjuice middleware compacted 68,289 chars of Bash output to 1,126 chars and returned that compacted text via Codex feedback (`exitCode: 2`, empty stdout).

Observed result after fix: The native Codex relay preserves no-op output for unchanged middleware results and returns Codex feedback only when middleware changes model-visible text. Actual Tokenjuice compaction now produces compacted feedback instead of the middleware post-processing error fallback.

What was not tested: A full live Codex agent turn with external model/provider credentials. The native hook boundary was replayed locally with the actual bundled Tokenjuice middleware.

<details>
<summary>Exact Tokenjuice native relay replay</summary>

```bash
node --import tsx <<'EOF'
import { createEmptyPluginRegistry } from './src/plugins/registry-empty.ts';
import { setActivePluginRegistry } from './src/plugins/runtime.ts';
import { createTokenjuiceAgentToolResultMiddleware } from './extensions/tokenjuice/tool-result-middleware.ts';
import { invokeNativeHookRelay, registerNativeHookRelay, testing } from './src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.ts';

const largeOutput = Array.from({ length: 400 }, (_, index) => `line ${index}: ${'x'.repeat(160)}`).join('\n');
const middleware = createTokenjuiceAgentToolResultMiddleware();
const registry = createEmptyPluginRegistry();
registry.agentToolResultMiddlewares.push({
  pluginId: 'tokenjuice',
  pluginName: 'tokenjuice',
  rawHandler: middleware,
  handler: middleware,
  runtimes: ['codex'],
  source: 'proof',
});
setActivePluginRegistry(registry);
const relay = registerNativeHookRelay({
  provider: 'codex',
  agentId: 'proof-agent',
  sessionId: 'proof-session',
  sessionKey: 'agent:proof:session',
  runId: 'proof-run',
});
const response = await invokeNativeHookRelay({
  provider: 'codex',
  relayId: relay.relayId,
  event: 'post_tool_use',
  rawPayload: {
    hook_event_name: 'PostToolUse',
    cwd: process.cwd(),
    turn_id: 'proof-turn',
    tool_name: 'Bash',
    tool_use_id: 'proof-call',
    tool_input: { command: 'cat big.log' },
    tool_response: { output: largeOutput, exit_code: 0 },
  },
});
relay.unregister();
testing.clearNativeHookRelaysForTests();
setActivePluginRegistry(createEmptyPluginRegistry());
console.log(JSON.stringify({
  exitCode: response.exitCode,
  stdoutBytes: response.stdout.length,
  stderrChars: response.stderr.length,
  originalChars: largeOutput.length,
  stderrPreview: response.stderr.slice(0, 240),
}, null, 2));
EOF
```

</details>
